identificationRemarks: This is the aptly named Angelica lineariloba (for the very narrow, linear leaf lobes). A. capitellata will have wider leaf lobes. When the flowers appear, this will have a wide, open umbel rather than the tight "buttons" or "heads" of A. capitellata. Also, this is a dry, hillside habitat; A. capitellata likes to keep it's feet moist or wet in stream and meadow habitats.
